@startuml chess-coach-multiplayer
' SPEC: _spec/chess-coach/multiplayer.puml
!includeurl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/proveo-ca/identity/refs/heads/main/proveo.iuml
skinparam componentStyle rectangle

title Chess Coach · Serverless LAN/Online Multiplayer\n(host-hub over Tailscale + WebRTC — no backend)

actor "Player 1\n(room creator / host)" as P1User
actor "Player 2" as P2User
actor "Observer ×0–4\n(optional)" as ObsUser

package "Tailscale tailnet  (100.x — WireGuard overlay, no NAT)" {

  package "Host browser = room authority" as HostPkg {
    [SolidJS UI · LanScreen\n(history nav · game-over end screen)] as HostUI
    [TailscaleChecklist\n(onboarding gate)] as Onboard
    [useMultiplayerGame\n(authoritative gameStore)] as HostHook
    [roomStore\n(seats · colors · started · identities)] as HostRoom
    [HostHubTransport\n(1→N RTCDataChannel)] as HostHub
    [useLanGameRecorder + useLivePreAnalysis\n→ gameHistoryStore + analysis cache] as HostRec
  }

  package "Guest browser = player / observer" as BlackPkg {
    [SolidJS UI · LanScreen\n(history nav · game-over end screen)] as BlackUI
    [useMultiplayerGame\n(mirror gameStore)] as BlackHook
    [GuestLinkTransport\n(1 link to host)] as BlackLink
    [useLanGameRecorder + useLivePreAnalysis\n→ gameHistoryStore + analysis cache] as BlackRec
  }

  package "Observer browser ×0–4  (read-only)" as ObsPkg {
    [SolidJS UI · LanScreen] as ObsUI
    [GuestLinkTransport] as ObsLink
  }
}

' ── Players drive their own browser ──
P1User --> HostUI  : "Create room · pick color · move · Start"
P2User --> BlackUI : "Join · pick/swap color · move · Start"
ObsUser --> ObsUI  : "Join (spectate)"

' ── Onboarding: gate the lobby on tailnet connectivity ──
HostUI   --> Onboard : "wraps room setup (step 3)"
Onboard  ..> Onboard : "detectPlatform() — UA → install help\nprobeTailnet() — 100.x ICE candidate (best-effort)"

' ── Host-side wiring ──
HostUI   --> HostHook
HostHook --> HostRoom : "seats · colors · swap · observer cap ≤4 · start gate"
HostHook --> HostHub  : "broadcast(RoomState · MoveApplied)"
HostUI   --> HostRec  : "each player records their own game"

' ── Guest-side wiring ──
BlackUI   --> BlackHook
BlackHook --> BlackLink : "send(Hello · ClaimColor · Move · StartRequest)"
BlackUI   --> BlackRec  : "each player records their own game"

' ── Data path: direct P2P over the tailnet, host = hub ──
BlackLink <-> HostHub : "RTCDataChannel\n(moves · room state)\nhost ICE candidate 100.x"
ObsLink   <-> HostHub : "RTCDataChannel\n(room-state broadcast)"

note bottom of HostHub
  **Serverless.** No Ktor / no relay / no STUN / no TURN.
  Tailscale supplies mutual 100.x reachability, so WebRTC
  connects directly via host ICE candidates.
  Signaling is MANUAL & out-of-band, one exchange per joiner:
    host offer → QR/link ──scan──▶ joiner answer → QR/link ──scan──▶ host
  Non-trickle ICE → each offer/answer fits a single QR.
  SDP is MINIFIED (keep only ICE ufrag/pwd, DTLS fingerprint,
  setup role + candidate lines; rebuild the fixed boilerplate on
  decode — browsers accept a canonical remote desc), then
  lz-string-compressed (transit-safe, no '+'). ~half the link
  size; verified to parse on Chromium/WebKit/Firefox, with a raw
  fallback for any SDP that doesn't fit the expected shape.
end note

note right of Onboard
  3-step collapsible (services/platform.ts, services/tailscale.ts):
    1. **Verify connected** — probeTailnet() looks for a 100.64.0.0/10
       host ICE candidate. Browsers may hide it, so detection is
       best-effort + a manual "I'm connected" override.
    2. **Get it running** — UA-tailored install steps + download/docs
       links (desktop Linux/macOS/Windows · mobile iOS/Android).
    3. **Choose side & invite** — the room setup (seats + invite link
       and scannable QR). Gated until step 1 is satisfied.
end note

note bottom of HostRoom
  Host browser **is** the room (authority); if it closes, the room ends.
  Seats: two players + observers ≤4 (optional).
  **Colors are NOT assigned by default** — each player picks White
  or Black in the lobby and may select the opposite seat to swap.
  Any color change resets both ready votes. Both players must agree
  on colors and press **Start Game**. Overflow joiners get ROOM_FULL.
  **Recoverable drop:** RTC "disconnected"/"failed" is held (seat kept,
  status = reconnecting) for a 15s grace window — ICE may re-validate
  the path on its own (restartIce() nudged on foreground) — before the
  game is declared over. Terminal "closed" ends it immediately.
end note

note top of HostPkg
  Pure **human-vs-human**: no AI opponent, no coach/LLM, no harness —
  CoachService / postMove are never invoked.
  Ships in the client-only web / PWA build over HTTPS.
end note

note bottom of BlackRec
  **Reviewable like a Coach game.** Each player's browser records the
  live game (useLanGameRecorder, driven by roomStore/gameStore — the
  coach-signal-based useGameRecorder doesn't fit the engine-free board)
  and warms per-ply analysis at background priority (useLivePreAnalysis,
  via the shared EnginePool — the only Stockfish use in LAN, for review
  only). On game over the record is finalized; the end screen links to
  /review/:id. History-nav buttons step through past plies WITHOUT the
  eval bar; relayed moves snap the view back to live so the shared game
  is never branched.
end note

@enduml
